<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
DOT damage has been normalized once again. The values for DOTs have been changed back to the current live settings - but the additions of stacking for Sorcerer/Cabalist/Wizards have been reatined. The casting-stat bonus has been retained as well, but has been tuned to give the correct bonus damage. The end result is that now all spellcasters casting a DOT spell will see a 0-35% bonus to their damage, based on their prime casting stat. To clarify a point of <BR>confusion, AE DoTs and spec DoTs in the same list do not stack. Higher <BR>damage DoTs will always overwrite lower damage versions in the same line<P><BR>Well 35% boost but it is Variable is this correct Bullseye? Can range  based on our INT Stat right?<P>--------------------<P>Griffin Shadowfeather<BR>38 Sorcecer, Galahad
</FONT>
