Patch 1.51J is not well thought out.<P>Minstrels, even with stealth, cannot be expected to have a 5 second cast half duration ae mezz compete against the instas and full duration mezzes from other speed classes (skalds and bards). This proposed spell is of only marginal use in PvE and even less use in RvR.<P>What encounter in PvE would find a 5 second cast time for a 26 second spell a useful thing?<P>What encounter in RvR would not make the casting of such a spell an invitation to be insta'd and farmed for rps by the opposing realm?<P>Leave Sorcs as the ae CC in Albion and make them a better class. If you feel you need do do something for Minstrels, fix the interface problems that have been a source of complaint since day 1.
