"With a group puller, 5 seconds is more than enough to prep and cast an AOE on the pull. this change brings them doen a bit in RvR, but it does not diminish the amount they might push us out of Groups."<P>Every single Minstrel I've talked to has laughed at the new 5-second requirement.  The difference between 3-sec and 5-sec is huge.<P>In addition, I've been told that this spell costs a Minstresl 20-25% of their power PER CAST.<P>So instead of a large group of monsters mezzed 60 feet away from your group for over a minute, you have a large group of monsters mezzed 10 feet away from your group for 29 seconds.<P>The long cast time and low duration pretty  much negates any chance of a remez.  A 5-second cast for a 14-second remez?  I think not.  That is also assuming they could even get the mez off since the monsters are so close to the party already.<P>If you want to test out just how bad a 5-second cast time with 29-second duration is, go to tanglers and do this:<P>Have someone pull, then spamcast a baseline debuff (2-sec cast), then switch to your 14th-Mind spec AE (30 sec duration).<P>Let me know how close they get to the party and how well you fare.
