<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Aye, Sorcerer's hit on a good point.  Why is it, when they try to help a class, instead of addressing their issues, they give them something theoretically good but something they didn't want?<P>Minstrels didn't want an AE Mez, like ya said.  Before it looked overpowering, and now it's nerfed to oblivion.  It should have been removed and *replaced* with something that Minstrels *did* want, instead of leaving it there in it's gimped state.  Kind of like a corpse, it just sits there to remind you.<P>And then Bards, did Bards ever ask for an Insta-AE-Mez??  No, if I recall their main concern was that all they do is run/rez/mez.  They can't kill anyone!  Or so that's their story.  Instead, they're given an Insta-AE-Mez??  It's a great ability, actually it being Insta *and* CC makes it *the* best ability next to Assassin-Stealth.  But hell, it doesn't address their concerns.<P>And for us, our Matter line.  They tried to do the right thing, by acknowledging that Matter is gimped.  But what did they give us?  Was it what we were calling for?  Something worth having?  No, it was more of the same which made the line not worth speccing in the first place!
</FONT>
